dom-ariamixin-ariaatomic.name: ariaAtomic
dom-ariamixin-ariaatomic.summary: The ariaAtomic property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-atomic attribute, which indicates whether assistive technologies will present all, or only parts of, the changed region based on the change notifications defined by the aria-relevant attribute.
dom-ariamixin-ariaatomic.title: Element.ariaAtomic

dom-ariamixin-ariaautocomplete.name: ariaAutoComplete
dom-ariamixin-ariaautocomplete.summary: The ariaAutoComplete property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-autocomplete attribute, which indicates whether inputting text could trigger display of one or more predictions of the user's intended value for a combobox, searchbox, or textbox and specifies how predictions would be presented if they were made.
dom-ariamixin-ariaautocomplete.title: Element.ariaAutoComplete

dom-ariamixin-ariabusy.name: ariaBusy
dom-ariamixin-ariabusy.summary: The ariaBusy property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-busy attribute, which indicates whether an element is being modified, as assistive technologies may want to wait until the modifications are complete before exposing them to the user.
dom-ariamixin-ariabusy.title: Element.ariaBusy

dom-ariamixin-ariachecked.name: ariaChecked
dom-ariamixin-ariachecked.summary: The ariaChecked property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-checked attribute, which indicates the current "checked" state of checkboxes, radio buttons, and other widgets that have a checked state.
dom-ariamixin-ariachecked.title: Element.ariaChecked

dom-ariamixin-ariacolcount.name: ariaColCount
dom-ariamixin-ariacolcount.summary: The ariaColCount property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-colcount attribute, which defines the number of columns in a table, grid, or treegrid.
dom-ariamixin-ariacolcount.title: Element.ariaColCount

dom-ariamixin-ariacolindex.name: ariaColIndex
dom-ariamixin-ariacolindex.summary: The ariaColIndex property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-colindex attribute, which defines an element's column index or position with respect to the total number of columns within a table, grid, or treegrid.
dom-ariamixin-ariacolindex.title: Element.ariaColIndex

dom-ariamixin-ariacolspan.name: ariaColSpan
dom-ariamixin-ariacolspan.summary: The ariaColSpan property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-colspan attribute, which defines the number of columns spanned by a cell or gridcell within a table, grid, or treegrid.
dom-ariamixin-ariacolspan.title: Element.ariaColSpan

dom-ariamixin-ariacurrent.name: ariaCurrent
dom-ariamixin-ariacurrent.summary: The ariaCurrent property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-current attribute, which indicates the element that represents the current item within a container or set of related elements.
dom-ariamixin-ariacurrent.title: Element.ariaCurrent

dom-ariamixin-ariadescription.name: ariaDescription
dom-ariamixin-ariadescription.summary: The ariaDescription property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-description attribute, which defines a string value that describes or annotates the current element.
dom-ariamixin-ariadescription.title: Element.ariaDescription

dom-ariamixin-ariadisabled.name: ariaDisabled
dom-ariamixin-ariadisabled.summary: The ariaDisabled property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-disabled attribute, which indicates that the element is perceivable but disabled, so it is not editable or otherwise operable.
dom-ariamixin-ariadisabled.title: Element.ariaDisabled

dom-ariamixin-ariaexpanded.name: ariaExpanded
dom-ariamixin-ariaexpanded.summary: The ariaExpanded property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-expanded attribute, which indicates whether a grouping element owned or controlled by this element is expanded or collapsed.
dom-ariamixin-ariaexpanded.title: Element.ariaExpanded

dom-ariamixin-ariahaspopup.name: ariaHasPopup
dom-ariamixin-ariahaspopup.summary: The ariaHasPopup property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-haspopup attribute, which indicates the availability and type of interactive popup element, such as menu or dialog, that can be triggered by an element.
dom-ariamixin-ariahaspopup.title: Element.ariaHasPopup

dom-ariamixin-ariahidden.name: ariaHidden
dom-ariamixin-ariahidden.summary: The ariaHidden property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-hidden attribute, which indicates whether the element is exposed to an accessibility API.
dom-ariamixin-ariahidden.title: Element.ariaHidden

dom-ariamixin-ariakeyshortcuts.name: ariaKeyShortcuts
dom-ariamixin-ariakeyshortcuts.summary: The ariaKeyShortcuts property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-keyshortcuts attribute, which indicates keyboard shortcuts that an author has implemented to activate or give focus to an element.
dom-ariamixin-ariakeyshortcuts.title: Element.ariaKeyShortcuts

dom-ariamixin-arialabel.name: ariaLabel
dom-ariamixin-arialabel.summary: The ariaLabel property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-label attribute, which defines a string value that labels the current element.
dom-ariamixin-arialabel.title: Element.ariaLabel

dom-ariamixin-arialevel.name: ariaLevel
dom-ariamixin-arialevel.summary: The ariaLevel property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-level attribute, which defines the hierarchical level of an element within a structure.
dom-ariamixin-arialevel.title: Element.ariaLevel

dom-ariamixin-arialive.name: ariaLive
dom-ariamixin-arialive.summary: The ariaLive property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-live attribute, which indicates that an element will be updated, and describes the types of updates the user agents, assistive technologies, and user can expect from the live region.
dom-ariamixin-arialive.title: Element.ariaLive

dom-ariamixin-ariamodal.name: ariaModal
dom-ariamixin-ariamodal.summary: The ariaModal property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-modal attribute, which indicates whether an element is modal when displayed.
dom-ariamixin-ariamodal.title: Element.ariaModal

dom-ariamixin-ariamultiline.name: ariaMultiLine
dom-ariamixin-ariamultiline.summary: The ariaMultiline property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-multiline attribute, which indicates whether a text box accepts multiple lines of input or only a single line.
dom-ariamixin-ariamultiline.title: Element.ariaMultiline

dom-ariamixin-ariamultiselectable.name: ariaMultiSelectable
dom-ariamixin-ariamultiselectable.summary: The ariaMultiSelectable property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-multiselectable attribute, which indicates that the user may select more than one item from the current selectable descendants.
dom-ariamixin-ariamultiselectable.title: Element.ariaMultiSelectable

dom-ariamixin-ariaorientation.name: ariaOrientation
dom-ariamixin-ariaorientation.summary: The ariaOrientation property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-orientation attribute, which indicates whether the element's orientation is horizontal, vertical, or unknown/ambiguous.
dom-ariamixin-ariaorientation.title: Element.ariaOrientation

dom-ariamixin-ariaorientation.name: ariaRoleDescription
dom-ariamixin-ariaorientation.summary: The ariaRoleDescription property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-roledescription attribute, which defines a human-readable, author-localized description for the role of an element.
dom-ariamixin-ariaorientation.title: Element.ariaRoleDescription

dom-ariamixin-ariaplaceholder.name: ariaPlaceholder
dom-ariamixin-ariaplaceholder.summary: The ariaPlaceholder property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-placeholder attribute, which defines a short hint intended to aid the user with data entry when the control has no value.
dom-ariamixin-ariaplaceholder.title: Element.ariaPlaceholder

dom-ariamixin-ariaposinset.name: ariaPosInSet
dom-ariamixin-ariaposinset.summary: The ariaPosInSet property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-posinset attribute, which defines an element's number or position in the current set of listitems or treeitems.
dom-ariamixin-ariaposinset.title: Element.ariaPosInSet

dom-ariamixin-ariapressed.name: ariaPressed
dom-ariamixin-ariapressed.summary: The ariaPressed property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-pressed attribute, which indicates the current "pressed" state of toggle buttons.
dom-ariamixin-ariapressed.title: Element.ariaPressed

dom-ariamixin-ariareadonly.name: ariaReadOnly
dom-ariamixin-ariareadonly.summary: The ariaReadOnly property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-readonly attribute, which indicates that the element is not editable, but is otherwise operable.
dom-ariamixin-ariareadonly.title: Element.ariaReadOnly

dom-ariamixin-ariarequired.name: ariaRequired
dom-ariamixin-ariarequired.summary: The ariaRequired property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-required attribute, which indicates that user input is required on the element before a form may be submitted.
dom-ariamixin-ariarequired.title: Element.ariaRequired

dom-ariamixin-ariarowcount.name: ariaRowCount
dom-ariamixin-ariarowcount.summary: The ariaRowCount property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-rowcount attribute, which defines the total number of rows in a table, grid, or treegrid.
dom-ariamixin-ariarowcount.title: Element.ariaRowCount

dom-ariamixin-ariarowindex.name: ariaRowIndex
dom-ariamixin-ariarowindex.summary: The ariaRowIndex property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-rowindex attribute, which defines an element's row index or position with respect to the total number of rows within a table, grid, or treegrid.
dom-ariamixin-ariarowindex.title: Element.ariaRowIndex

dom-ariamixin-ariarowspan.name: ariaRowSpan
dom-ariamixin-ariarowspan.summary: The ariaRowSpan property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-rowspan attribute, which defines the number of rows spanned by a cell or gridcell within a table, grid, or treegrid.
dom-ariamixin-ariarowspan.title: Element.ariaRowSpan

dom-ariamixin-ariavaluemax.name: ariaSelected
dom-ariamixin-ariavaluemax.summary: The ariaSelected property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-selected attribute, which indicates the current "selected" state of elements that have a selected state.
dom-ariamixin-ariavaluemax.title: Element.ariaSelected

dom-ariamixin-ariavaluemax.name: ariaValueMax
dom-ariamixin-ariavaluemax.summary: The ariaValueMax property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-valuemax attribute, which defines the maximum allowed value for a range widget.
dom-ariamixin-ariavaluemax.title: Element.ariaValueMax

dom-ariamixin-ariasetsize.name: ariaSetSize
dom-ariamixin-ariasetsize.summary: The ariaSetSize property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-setsize attribute, which defines the number of items in the current set of listitems or treeitems.
dom-ariamixin-ariasetsize.title: Element.ariaSetSize

dom-ariamixin-ariasort.name: ariaSort
dom-ariamixin-ariasort.summary: The ariaSort property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-sort attribute, which indicates if items in a table or grid are sorted in ascending or descending order.
dom-ariamixin-ariasort.title: Element.ariaSort

dom-ariamixin-ariavaluemin.name: ariaValueMin
dom-ariamixin-ariavaluemin.summary: The ariaValueMin property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-valuemin attribute, which defines the minimum allowed value for a range widget.
dom-ariamixin-ariavaluemin.title: Element.ariaValueMin

dom-ariamixin-ariavaluenow.name: ariaValueNow
dom-ariamixin-ariavaluenow.summary: The ariaValueNow property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-valuenow attribute, which defines the current value for a range widget.
dom-ariamixin-ariavaluenow.title: Element.ariaValueNow

dom-ariamixin-ariavaluetext.name: ariaValueText
dom-ariamixin-ariavaluetext.summary: The ariaValueText property of the Element interface reflects the value of the aria-valuetext attribute, which defines the human readable text alternative of aria-valuenow for a range widget.
dom-ariamixin-ariavaluetext.title: Element.ariaValueText
